heaviest_rainrate.status: The rain rate reached 27.0mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

summary.description:
Today, a bit warmer for the feels like temperature (up 4.9°C) and outside temperature (up 3.8°C) and more moisture-laden outside humidity (up 8%) and rainfall (up 0.3 mm).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in cloud levels (up 595 m) and light levels (up 2546 lux).

The past week and month had observable variation in cloud levels (up 999 m) and light levels (up 6305 lux) when compared to today.
